content:
Choose how you want to deploy this model:

Deploy as a new model within a new prediction definition: Create a prediction definition with this model. Optionally, change the default name of the prediction definition.

Add model to an existing prediction definition: Deploy this model to an existing prediction definition that you select.

Update an existing model: Replace an existing model. Einstein detects and selects the model that was most recently deployed from a previous version of this model.

Depending on your selection:

To deploy the model to a new prediction definition, specify the new model name and new prediction definition.

To deploy as a new model to an existing prediction definition, specify the model name, and then select the target prediction definition from the list.

To replace a deployed model, select the target model from the list. Click Next.

If you replace a deployed model, you proceed directly to Review Your Selections and Deploy the Model. Otherwise, you proceed to Select Whether to Connect to a Salesforce Object.

Specify the new model name and new prediction definition, or select an existing prediction definition to add or update a model.
title: Deploying Prediction Models in Salesforce Analytics
